Stifel Financial Corp said itreceived an unsolicited merger proposal from privately heldLaidlaw Adams and Peck Inc for 15 dlrs a share in cash for allits outstanding shares.    The proposal, which expires July 1, values Stifel at about54 mln dlrs.    Stifel has about 3.6 mln shares outstanding.    The company said its management and board of directors willconsider the proposal but have not set a date to meet.    It said the proposal is currently being studied by GoldmanSachs and Co and legal counsel.    It said conditions of the proposal include obtainingnecessary financing, satisfactory completion of a due diligenceinvestigation by Laidlaw, and execution of employment contractswith key employees to be designated by Laidlaw. Reuter&#3;